# GITHUB.md — GitHub Access Config
#
# Copy this file to GITHUB.md and fill in your values.
# GITHUB.md is gitignored — it never gets committed.
#
# This is how the agent knows which accounts and repos it can access.
# Update it after running scripts/setup-github.sh.

## Accounts

- **Account 1:** username=your-username, type=user
- **Account 2:** username=your-org, type=org

## Orgs & Repos

- your-username → personal repos
- your-org → org repos

## Access Status

- Account 1: ✅ token configured
- Account 2: ✅ token configured

## Red Lines

- NEVER delete any repository. Ever.
- Never force-push to main/master without explicit approval
- Never expose tokens or credentials in commits or chat output

## Notes

_(Add anything the agent needs to know — e.g. which repos are active, branch conventions, etc.)_
